    "tags": ["US-China AI rivalry", "Export controls", "Iran sanctions", "Strait of Hormuz", "Model theft"],
    "fresh": true,
    "content": "**Geopolitiks Snacks** — April 26, 2026\n\n---\n\n## 🧷 Washington Says China Is Distilling American AI by the Industrial Barrel\n\nThe White House has reached the \"our models are being stolen at scale\" stage of the AI rivalry, which usually means more memos and sanctions are loading.\n\n- **The accusation:** In an April 23 memo, science adviser Michael Kratsios said entities \"principally based in China\" are running industrial-scale campaigns to distill capabilities from closed U.S. AI systems.\n- **The policy follow-through:** AP reports the memo landed the same week the House Foreign Affairs Committee backed a bipartisan bill to identify foreign actors extracting key features from U.S. models and punish them, including with sanctions.\n\n*The AI race is now part benchmark war, part export-control paperwork, and part intellectual-property panic. Efficient.*\n\n**Sources:** [AP News](https://apnews.com/article/ai-china-us-model-distillation-kratsios-a5c40346394ef5fa9ae710c5aabdc62c) | [Select Committee on the CCP](https://chinaselectcommittee.house.gov/media/press-releases/moolenaar-backs-house-committee-s-passage-of-export-control-legislation-to-counter-ccp-threats)\n\n---\n\n## 🛑 Congress Suddenly Remembered AI Chips Are Strategic\n\nThe House Foreign Affairs Committee spent April 22 rediscovering that maybe you shouldn't let advanced semiconductors casually drift toward Beijing.\n\n- **What advanced:** The committee moved export-control legislation aimed at restricting semiconductor manufacturing equipment, cracking down on chip smuggling, protecting whistleblowers and authorizing sanctions for AI model theft.\n- **Why now:** Bloomberg reported lawmakers are trying to close loopholes that they believe still let China access powerful U.S. technology, including Nvidia chips, even as the administration has held back from major new curbs.\n\n*Sell the chips, investigate the loopholes, sanction the theft, repeat until strategy appears.*\n\n**Sources:** [Select Committee on the CCP](https://chinaselectcommittee.house.gov/media/press-releases/moolenaar-backs-house-committee-s-passage-of-export-control-legislation-to-counter-ccp-threats) | [Japan Times via Bloomberg](https://www.japantimes.co.jp/business/2026/04/23/tech/ai-export-control-china-us-house/)\n\n---\n\n## 🚢 The Ceasefire Now Includes Boarding Tankers, Apparently\n\nThe U.S.-Iran \"ceasefire\" continues to have a very active interpretation section.\n\n- **The seizure:** AP reports U.S. forces boarded the M/T Tifani in the Bay of Bengal after the Pentagon said it was a sanctioned vessel carrying Iranian oil. It was the second Iran-linked ship interdicted by the U.S. military.\n- **The message:** The Pentagon said global maritime enforcement against vessels providing material support to Iran will continue \"anywhere they operate,\" while legal experts told AP the truce has no formal written terms and is therefore open to everyone's favorite pastime: creative interpretation.\n\n*Nothing says de-escalation like turning the Indian Ocean into sanctions enforcement improv.*\n\n**Sources:** [AP News](https://apnews.com/article/iran-war-tifani-sanctioned-ship-bd0190ae22d133d85f331cb300b179bf)\n\n---\n\n## 💣 Reopening Hormuz May Take Longer Than the Press Briefing\n\nWashington is trying to restore confidence in the world's most nerve-wracking shipping lane. Confidence, sadly, is not a minesweeper.\n\n- **The timeline problem:** AP reports Pentagon officials told lawmakers it could take six months to clear possible Iranian mines in the Strait of Hormuz, even as the administration pushes to get traffic moving again.\n- **The stakes:** Roughly 20% of the world's oil normally passes through the strait, and the U.S. has already surged mine-clearing assets, including two Avenger-class minesweepers departing from Japan.\n\n*Clearing the mines is hard. Convincing insurers the mines are gone may be the actually impossible part.*\n\n**Sources:** [AP News](https://apnews.com/article/iran-war-strait-hormuz-minesweeping-navy-underwater-edef3201f6e227c4b5e5edf1a28f6f77)"
  }
]
